{
  "stem": "25912.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the group consisted of my mother and myself, the wife of a Polish officer, a friend of my father's, another wife of an officer with a six-year-old daughter, and a boy of 14, the orphaned son of my father's commanding officer, whose mother had died during the war.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it was a sort of slightly ill-assorted group.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What we hadn't realized-- or I'm sure my father didn't know-- that these people had no means of getting us out of Poland, other than what I would call chutzpah.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "First, they took us to Katowice, to some Jewish organization which was smuggling survivors to Israel.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But of course, maybe by some stretch, we could have qualified, but nobody else in the group.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we left there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we went to a border town with Czechoslovakia, where our guides proceeded to try and hitchhike out of-- with us out of Poland, stopping Russian lorries and trying to bribe them to give us a lift.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Does Linz-- is it the other side of Czechoslovakia, isn't it?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they were supposed to take us to the, to the frontier.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, we finally got a lift.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We got on a Russian lorry, were hidden in the back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Russians said not to worry, the Poles will not stop them at the frontier, drove into Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that evening-- we didn't get very far in Czechoslovakia-- they stopped.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they said out, not going any further.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we're left in the middle of nowhere-- strange group, women, children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We promptly got arrested by the Czech police, who decided that we were German spies.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They took us to the local police station.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were all drunk-- set us on benches with guns facing us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was absolute nightmare.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, they were just completely stupid.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
